    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-07-01T21:17:38+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-01T21:17:38+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-01T11:47:38Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-01T11:47:38Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A series of low pressure systems passing over waters to the south will extend cold fronts that will cross over SA through to the end of the week. A high pressure system is then forecast to move into the Bight from late Friday and extend a ridge across the state over the weekend, as it slowly moves southeastwards towards Tasmania.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW009" description="Flinders" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <warning-summary type="sheep_graziers_warning" start-time-local="2026-07-01T16:34:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-03T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-01T07:04:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-02T14:30:00Z">Warning to Sheep Graziers</warning-summary>
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-07-01T21:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-02T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-01T11:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-01T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly clear. Winds northwesterly 25 to 40 km/h.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-07-02T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-03T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-01T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-02T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers near the coast, medium chance elsewhere. Winds northwesterly 25 to 40 km/h turning westerly in the early afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 5 and 8 with daytime temperatures reaching between 12 and 17.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection not recommended, UV Index predicted to reach 2 [Low]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-07-03T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-04T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-02T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-03T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Slight chance of a shower. Winds westerly 20 to 30 km/h tending southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h in the morning then becoming light in the late afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 3 and 7 with daytime temperatures reaching between 11 and 15.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-07-04T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-05T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-03T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-04T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. The chance of morning fog south of Hawker. Slight chance of a shower on and east of the ranges, near zero chance elsewhere. Light winds becoming southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h during the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to between 3 and 7 with daytime temperatures reaching between 11 and 15.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-07-05T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-06T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-04T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-05T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Slight chance of a shower on and east of the ranges, near zero chance elsewhere. Winds east to southeasterly 20 to 30 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to around 5 with daytime temperatures reaching between 10 and 15.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
